# Frontend styles: no multi-line comments in source (`/* ... */`)

## Rule

When modifying frontend style sources (`.css`, `.scss`, `.less`), **never** use multi-line comments in the `/* ... */` form.

## Why

Sass/Less can emit `/* ... */` comments into the compiled CSS output, which can:
- ship internal notes in production assets
- interfere with expected minification output during gulp compilation

## Requirements

- Never use multi-line / block comments (including `/*! ... */`) in `.css`, `.scss`, or `.less`.
  - Disallowed example: `/* Cursor: keep payment method wrapper transparent for flex/order layout */`
- Prefer communicating rationale in:
  - an issue/ticket comment, or
  - module/theme documentation (`README.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`), or
  - the PR/commit description (when applicable).

## Allowed comment format (source-only, keep minimal)

- If you must leave a short note while iterating, use single-line comments only in this format:
  - `// ...`

Notes:
- `// ...` is valid in SCSS and LESS, but **not** in plain CSS.
- Therefore, in `.css` files: do not add comments at all.
